00:48:59,220 --> 00:49:03,457
The politicians requested for
National Merit to be awarded to both men.

777
00:49:06,902 --> 00:49:07,878
Where's his son?

778
00:49:08,058 --> 00:49:09,513
I heard he was on
the bus with his father.

779
00:49:09,709 --> 00:49:11,219
We have to interview him.

780
00:49:11,304 --> 00:49:13,724
I know. I heard that he
evacuated all the passengers.

781
00:49:13,809 --> 00:49:15,511
Where is he?

782
00:49:15,786 --> 00:49:18,550
The assemblyman would like to
give him the words of comfort.

783
00:49:18,635 --> 00:49:22,292
Mr. Kim. Did you take a picture of the
Assemblyman paying his condolences?

784
00:49:22,872 --> 00:49:24,636
Yes. We took it.
Did you take it?

785
00:49:24,721 --> 00:49:25,703
Let's go.

786
00:49:25,788 --> 00:49:26,622
Let's go.

787
00:49:44,860 --> 00:49:45,732
Mr. Choi.

788
00:49:49,488 --> 00:49:51,055
He's out.

789
00:49:51,287 --> 00:49:52,988
I thought he was working too fast.

790
00:49:54,317 --> 00:49:55,392
No!

791
00:49:59,371 --> 00:50:01,231
Oh my goodness.

792
00:50:01,488 --> 00:50:02,788
My heart stopped.

793
00:50:06,321 --> 00:50:08,405
Did you have a bad dream?

794
00:50:10,397 --> 00:50:11,972
No. I wasn't sleeping.

795
00:50:12,057 --> 00:50:13,896
It seemed like you were crying just now.

796
00:50:15,468 --> 00:50:16,380
No, I wasn't.

797
00:50:26,480 --> 00:50:27,422
Wait a minute.

798
00:50:27,521 --> 00:50:29,369
Jaechan. Jaechan.
Get me out.

799
00:50:29,454 --> 00:50:32,654
I didn't do it. I didn't do it.

800
00:50:39,200 --> 00:50:40,120
Hello.

801
00:50:40,788 --> 00:50:41,796
Where are you right now?

802
00:50:42,867 --> 00:50:44,132
At school.

803
00:50:44,237 --> 00:50:45,390
You're okay, right?

804
00:50:45,475 --> 00:50:47,808
You're not sick or hurt, are you?

805
00:50:47,893 --> 00:50:48,698
No.

806
00:50:48,783 --> 00:50:49,546
Why do you ask?

807
00:50:51,747 --> 00:50:52,983
Never mind. It's fine if you're okay.

808
00:50:53,604 --> 00:50:54,586
What time are you coming home?

809
00:50:56,618 --> 00:50:58,415
I'm not sure. Around 10 PM maybe?

810
00:50:58,500 --> 00:51:00,165
Don't go anywhere else
and come straight home.

811
00:51:00,250 --> 00:51:00,957
Do you understand?

812
00:51:01,042 --> 00:51:02,251
Do you think I'm a fool?

813
00:51:02,336 --> 00:51:03,627
Where else would I go?

814
00:51:04,204 --> 00:51:05,262
Okay.

815
00:51:20,648 --> 00:51:22,325
I'm trying to save my mom.

816
00:51:22,410 --> 00:51:24,020
Dad has to disappear...

817
00:51:24,984 --> 00:51:26,583
...in order for my mom to live.

818
00:51:30,711 --> 00:51:32,517
Yes. It's just a dream.

819
00:51:32,617 --> 00:51:34,091
It's nothing.
It's nothing.

820
00:51:38,619 --> 00:51:39,850
Let me go!

821
00:51:39,950 --> 00:51:40,964
We can't.

822
00:51:42,683 --> 00:51:44,562
I asked you to believe me.

823
00:51:46,944 --> 00:51:49,973
We could've changed it
if you believed me.

824
00:51:56,111 --> 00:51:57,815
Seriously.

825
00:52:36,995 --> 00:52:40,924
I want you to make sure that
all the passengers get off.

826
00:52:42,251 --> 00:52:45,874
Once they get off, make sure that they
go as far away from the bus as possible.

827
00:52:45,959 --> 00:52:47,713
Let's not do that.
Let's just run away.

828
00:52:47,798 --> 00:52:49,718
It's exactly like my dream right now.

829
00:52:49,803 --> 00:52:51,341
I'm responsible for this bus.

830
00:52:51,426 --> 00:52:53,359
So, how can I just runaway to save myself.

831
00:52:53,699 --> 00:52:55,113
Father, please...

832
00:52:55,198 --> 00:52:55,817
You brat.

833
00:52:55,917 --> 00:52:58,113
If a catch doesn't catch
the ball and runs away...

834
00:52:58,198 --> 00:53:00,944
...the umpire will get hit by the ball.
Then it will be a mess.

835
00:53:02,294 --> 00:53:03,814
I'll grow out my hair.

836
00:53:04,697 --> 00:53:06,721
You said it's your wish
to see me with long hair.

837
00:53:08,868 --> 00:53:11,798
I'll grow out my hair.
So let's get off.

838
00:53:11,883 --> 00:53:12,754
Really?

839
00:53:14,246 --> 00:53:15,125
Okay.

840
00:53:16,147 --> 00:53:18,362
I'll see it later for sure.

841
00:53:20,086 --> 00:53:21,795
So get off the bus first.

842
00:54:01,281 --> 00:54:03,679
By the way, it wasn't
a son but a daughter?

843
00:54:04,487 --> 00:54:08,812
I heard that the child on the bus
wasn't a son but a daughter.

844
00:54:09,250 --> 00:54:10,717
-Is that right?
-Yes.

845
00:54:14,952 --> 00:54:17,687
Madam. Where's your
daughter right now?

846
00:54:22,013 --> 00:54:25,362
Hongjoo isn't here right now.

847
00:54:30,267 --> 00:54:31,935
Oh my goodness.

848
00:54:35,840 --> 00:54:38,208
What are you doing here at this hour?

849
00:54:40,817 --> 00:54:42,979
I didn't come here
because I changed my mind.

850
00:54:43,447 --> 00:54:45,949
I wanted to explain why
I won't believe you.

851
00:54:47,317 --> 00:54:48,318
Go ahead.

852
00:54:48,452 --> 00:54:49,619
I'm a prosecutor.

853
00:54:50,517 --> 00:54:53,090
My job is to punish the culprit
after the crime took place.

854
00:54:53,390 --> 00:54:54,591
It's not to stop the crime.

855
00:54:55,759 --> 00:54:57,105
I'm saying that there's nothing
I can do...

856
00:54:57,190 --> 00:54:58,962
...no matter how many times
you tell me your dream.

857
00:54:59,126 --> 00:55:01,161
It's not my business
no matter who dies in our dreams.

858
00:55:01,246 --> 00:55:02,932
And I don't need to be responsible
for them.

859
00:55:03,017 --> 00:55:03,872
But...

860
00:55:04,754 --> 00:55:05,600
But...

861
00:55:08,116 --> 00:55:09,609
You feel like you've
become a catcher, don't you?

862
00:55:16,650 --> 00:55:19,072
There's a ball coming at 160km per hour.

863
00:55:19,316 --> 00:55:20,851
It's scary catch it.

864
00:55:21,587 --> 00:55:23,420
But if you avoid it,
you'll mess up the game.

865
00:55:24,350 --> 00:55:25,288
It's like that, isn't it?

866
00:55:29,617 --> 00:55:30,445
That's right.

867
00:55:31,314 --> 00:55:33,292
Now even if I don't want to
believe it, I can't ignore it.

868
00:55:33,805 --> 00:55:35,910
Because I'm dreaming
those darn dreams too.

869
00:55:36,655 --> 00:55:38,502
Why did I start having those dreams too?

870
00:55:38,702 --> 00:55:39,290
Why me?

871
00:55:39,375 --> 00:55:41,575
I don't know why it had to be you either.

872
00:55:41,660 --> 00:55:43,532
I don't even know why I started
having these dreams either.

873
00:55:43,617 --> 00:55:44,981
So how would I know that?

874
00:55:45,402 --> 00:55:46,932
I don't know what it is,
but there must be a reason.

875
00:55:47,017 --> 00:55:48,427
A reason that you and I are
having those dreams...

876
00:56:34,651 --> 00:56:35,759
I don't know!

877
00:56:37,474 --> 00:56:39,963
But what are you going
to do if there's a reason?

878
00:56:40,264 --> 00:56:41,371
You can't stop them because
you're a prosecutor...

879
00:56:41,456 --> 00:56:42,974
...and you don't want to believe me.

880
00:56:43,059 --> 00:56:44,568
But you're saying that it's all my fault?

881
00:56:44,719 --> 00:56:46,303
Did you come here to tell me that?

882
00:56:52,350 --> 00:56:53,276
I need your help.

883
00:56:59,083 --> 00:57:00,984
You were in my dream.

884
00:57:02,543 --> 00:57:04,628
You blamed me for not listening to you...

885
00:57:04,713 --> 00:57:07,390
...and Seungwon got into a police car
or an ambulance and left.

886
00:57:08,650 --> 00:57:10,162
I just don't know what
that dream is about...

887
00:57:11,350 --> 00:57:12,362
Seungwon...

888
00:57:13,817 --> 00:57:15,131
Who is Seungwon?

889
00:57:16,256 --> 00:57:17,434
He's my younger brother.

890
00:57:17,817 --> 00:57:18,437
Why?

891
00:57:22,989 --> 00:57:24,076
In my dream...

892
00:57:24,982 --> 00:57:26,543
...the guy named Seungwon...

893
00:57:28,543 --> 00:57:30,125
...killed someone.

894
00:57:32,693 --> 00:57:33,460
Excuse me?

895
00:57:48,198 --> 00:57:51,950
"4 season antifreeze."

896
00:57:55,896 --> 00:57:57,041
Seungwon.

897
00:57:58,347 --> 00:57:59,011
Look at that.

898
00:57:59,377 --> 00:58:00,441
You memorized my name.

899
00:58:01,083 --> 00:58:03,054
Then he said it's
because of his brother...

900
00:58:03,139 --> 00:58:05,815
He said that he became
a murderer because of his brother.

901
00:58:08,879 --> 00:58:11,223
Then his older brother is you, Jaechan?

902
00:58:14,724 --> 00:58:17,124
Did you follow me?

903
00:58:18,595 --> 00:58:20,628
Yes. Let's go together.

904
00:58:20,713 --> 00:58:21,909
I'll take you home.

905
00:58:36,813 --> 00:58:42,219
"Nam Chuldoo"

906
00:59:02,239 --> 00:59:04,151
"While You Were Sleeping"

907
00:59:04,236 --> 00:59:06,026
Is it connected to
Park Junmo's case?

908
00:59:06,111 --> 00:59:06,912
It's because you
released Park Junmo...

909
00:59:06,997 --> 00:59:07,931
It's because of you.

910
00:59:08,016 --> 00:59:09,216
Do you have contact lenses?

911
00:59:09,316 --> 00:59:10,250
Do I look different without my glasses?

912
00:59:10,350 --> 00:59:11,117
Are you falling for me again?

913
00:59:11,202 --> 00:59:12,117
Isn't the case closed?

914
00:59:12,216 --> 00:59:13,393
I brought it back.

915
00:59:13,478 --> 00:59:14,850
I plan to dig into the case to the end.

916
00:59:14,950 --> 00:59:16,851
Why is it so hard for you to hear
that I'm looking forward to it?

917
00:59:16,950 --> 00:59:18,584
You're saying that you'll be
disappointed if I can't do it.

918
00:59:18,683 --> 00:59:19,384
But why is it me?

919
00:59:19,483 --> 00:59:21,317
Why don't you want to
disappoint me specifically?

920
00:59:21,416 --> 00:59:22,828
What do you do, Nam Hongjoo?

921
00:59:22,913 --> 00:59:24,449
Are you interested in me now?

922
00:59:24,510 --> 00:59:25,944
Are you saying that you
want to start dating me?

923
00:59:31,334 --> 00:59:44,218
"While You Were Sleeping"
